    "entity_id": "MGT-003",
    "name": "Patch Manager",
    "type": "ManagementTool",
    "subtype": "Patch Management Tool",
    "layer": "Management Layer",
    "description": "Enterprise software component responsible for the systematic discovery, acquisition, testing, scheduling, deployment, and verification of patches across operating systems, applications, firmware, and drivers on managed endpoint fleets. Integrates with vulnerability management platforms to prioritize patch deployment based on CVE severity, exploitability, and asset criticality. Maintains patch compliance state records and supports rollback capabilities for failed deployments.",
    "purpose": "Systematic orchestration of the endpoint patch lifecycle encompassing vulnerability-driven patch prioritization, patch acquisition from authoritative sources, controlled staging and testing, scheduled deployment across endpoint groups, installation verification, compliance state reporting, and rollback management for OS, application, driver, and firmware updates.",
